                    text: "The 4D56 (8V) is renowned for mechanical durability, especially in non-emissions-controlled markets. However, pre-1999 engines are prone to cylinder head cracking under thermal stress. Post-1999 revisions significantly improved head integrity. With proper cooling system care, quality diesel, and regular oil changes, these engines commonly exceed 300,000 km.",
