                    "@type": "Answer",
                    text: "Modest gains are possible. Carburettor rejetting or TBI remapping yields +8–12 kW, but the 8-valve head limits airflow. Bolt-ons (exhaust, performance carb) offer marginal gains. Significant tuning is impractical—most owners prioritize economy and reliability over performance.",
