                    text: "The 4G93 SOHC 16V is generally reliable with proper maintenance. Early models (1991–1996) had HLA wear issues, but post-1997 revisions improved durability. Its aluminum block and lack of turbo reduce major failure risks. Using correct 10W-40 oil and adhering to service intervals greatly enhances longevity.",
